        "@value": "DEFINITION: Relates an assignment to the resource it assigns."
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "EXAMPLE: Assignment of a person to a project."
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "NOTE: People, organizations, monetary amounts, equipment can all be assigned."
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "NOTE: While typically this predicate will be used with assignment subjects, there may be other use cases, and therefore a domain is not specified."
